snippet.textDisplay: Let me do the math for the expansion for sword and shield. Let's say you do not have the games. You now have to pay both games to get the full experience of the expansion. Sword and Shield cost about $60 each which is about $120. Then you have to pay for the Nintendo online membership which costs $20 for a year. Then you have to get both expansion passes to get all the Pokémon which cost $30 each which is another $60. You would be paying about $200 just to experience the full expansion. The only other way to experience the expansions is to have a friend with the other to trade you Pokémon locally. Not to mention Pokémon Home. Which we do not know how much that costs. So you may be spending more than $200 on Pokémon Sword and Shield. Them add Pokémon is just them addressing the Dexit controversy. snippet.textDisplay: I'm sorry Nintendo and Gamefreak, but I wish you didn't go this route.. Sending us a incomplete game and "giving it back" through DLC. You know Sword and Shield postgame is extremely barebones and, to be honest, if you delayed the game for at least the same amount of time that both DLCs come out, we could have gotten this DLC content in the base game for free and not have to dish out $30 AND not divide the fans in the process. With all the lies about game balancing, graphical fidelity, and your stance for why Pokemon were cut, I find it much harder to trust this company handling the Pokemon games even more now that they turned to expansion passes. But now that there's not much the fans can do at this point, the LEAST you guys can do is give us more things to do with the base game from now until the first DLC, because it's still 5 MONTHS AWAY.
